"## ChatSphere: A Real-Time Communication Platform with Enhanced Organization\n\nThis document reports on the development of ChatSphere, a real-time chat application created by Group 11 from the Computer Science department at IIIT Vadodara for the academic year 2025-2026, under the guidance of Dr. Pooja Mishra.\n\nThe primary objective of ChatSphere is to provide a secure, scalable, and user-friendly communication system that addresses the limitations of existing messaging platforms, particularly in terms of separating professional and personal conversations and managing messages and files effectively.\n\n**Key Features and Functionalities:**\n\nChatSphere distinguishes itself through a unique \"Work Mode\" and \"Private Mode\" system, allowing users to compartmentalize their professional and personal communications. The application offers a comprehensive set of features designed to enhance organization and user experience:\n\n*   **User Authentication:** A secure registration and login system, including a password recovery mechanism via security questions.\n*   **Mode Selection:** Users can seamlessly switch between Work Mode and Private Mode.\n*   **Communication Modes:** Supports both one-to-one direct messaging and group chats (organized into \"Rooms\").\n*   **Message Management:**\n    *   **Starred Messages:** Users can mark important messages and organize them into custom categories.\n    *   **Real-time Editing:** Allows for editing of sent messages.\n    *   **String-based Search:** Facilitates quick retrieval of past conversations.\n*   **File Storage:** An integrated file management system that allows users to upload, store, and categorize files.\n*   **User Interface:** Features a user-friendly UI with theme switching capabilities (dark and light modes) and a dedicated settings page for profile updates.\n\n**Technical Architecture and Implementation:**\n\nChatSphere is built upon a client-server architecture, utilizing a modern technology stack:\n\n*   **Frontend:** React with Vite\n*   **Backend:** Flask (Python)\n*   **Database:** SQLite with SQLAlchemy\n*   **File Storage:** Cloudinary\n\nThe development process involved detailed requirement analysis, including functional and non-functional requirements focusing on security, performance, usability, scalability, and reliability. The project's lifecycle encompassed UI/UX design, implementation of various modules (landing page, registration, login, forgot password, mode selection, chat functionalities, settings, theme switching), comprehensive testing (unit, integration, functional, UI), and deployment considerations.\n\n**Conclusion and Future Work:**\n\nThe project successfully delivered a structured and organized real-time messaging platform that meets its stated objectives. ChatSphere offers enhanced organization tools through categorized starred messages and file storage, addresses the need for separation of professional and personal communications, and provides a secure and user-friendly experience.\n\nPotential future enhancements for ChatSphere include the integration of voice/video calls, end-to-end encryption for increased security, push notifications, message reactions, AI-driven suggestions, cloud storage integration, and the development of an admin dashboard."